		<legis-type>A BILL</legis-type>
		<official-title>To amend title 11 of the United States Code to treat Puerto Rico as a State for purposes of chapter
			 9 of such title relating to the adjustment of debts of municipalities.</official-title>
	</form>
	<legis-body id="HD8D281F8BA124FD18D36B6DC3BB277BB" style="OLC">
		<section id="HDAAE26352C8E4508A2ACB84C3F1E69F5" section-type="section-one">
      <enum>1.</enum>
      <header>Short title</header>
      <text display-inline="no-display-inline">This Act may be cited as the <quote>
          <short-title>
            <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="act" value="Puerto Rico Chapter 9 Uniformity Act of 2014" proposed="true">Puerto Rico Chapter 9 Uniformity Act of 2014</cato:entity-ref>
          </short-title>
        </quote>.</text>
		</section>
    <section id="H2807A9E1BBF34880A3EEBD1457484921">
      <enum>2.</enum>
      <header>Amendment</header>
      <text display-inline="no-display-inline">
        <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="uscode" value="usc/11/101//52">
          <external-xref legal-doc="usc" parsable-cite="usc/11/101">Section 101(52)</external-xref> of title 11, United States Code</cato:entity-ref>, is amended to read as follows:</text>
			<quoted-block display-inline="no-display-inline" id="HE789B8372B1A4859B9628B9268D34495" style="traditional">
				<paragraph id="HCA3ABCA7A99141A1981CAB06112DC8E9">
          <enum>(52) </enum>
          <text display-inline="yes-display-inline">The term <quote>State</quote> includes Puerto Rico and, except for the purpose of defining who may be a debtor under <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="uscode" value="usc-chapter/11/9">chapter 9
			 of this title</cato:entity-ref>, includes the District of Columbia.</text>
        </paragraph>
        <after-quoted-block>.</after-quoted-block>
      </quoted-block>
		</section>
